    "At the Fuller Museum of Art in Brockton, MA, Abbott Thompson curated Bloom\u2019s work in a 1996 exhibit titled \u201cThe Spirit of Hyman Bloom: Sixty Years of Painting and Drawing.\u201d Abbott Thompson was widely known for her group shows, including \u201cLandscape as Metaphor: The Transcendental Vision\u201d(1993) at Fitchburg Art Museum and a series at the Concord Art Association titled \u201cThe Master Printers,\u201d \u201cExploring the Woodcut,\u201d and \u201cThe Unique Print.\u201d\u00a0Abbott Thompson had an art gallery for her own work from 1970 to 2010.": [],
